  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0d86\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4 18 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Who are the 18 ministers of the interim government?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "18 ministers of the new interim government of President Ranil Wickremesinghe took oath before the President at the Prime Minister's Office today (July 22).",
        "Here, Ali Sabri has the position of Minister of Foreign Affairs and Professor G.L. Peiris, who previously held that position, has not been included in the cabinet this time.",
        "Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna's chairman, Professor GL Peiris, has held senior ministerial positions in successive governments. But the name of Dallas Alahaperuma, who appeared for the election of the President of the Parliament held recently, was confirmed by GL Peiris.",
        "So far no new minister has been sworn in for the positions of defense and finance and accordingly the relevant subjects will be under the president."
      ],
